Former governor of Kano State, Senator Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso was not attacked during a political gathering in Kano yesterday, an aide of his political ally has said. Media Aide to the Kano governorship candidate of the PDP in the 2019 gubernatorial election, Abba Kabir Yusuf; Malam Ibrahim Adam said it was untrue that Kwankwaso was attacked after a meeting with the officials of PDP national committee for the ward congress and other factional leaders of the party in the state.  Kwankwaso may dump APC today Take it easy, you two ‘Why APC must reconcile Ganduje, Kwankwaso now’